  -- Specifically, distDeriv μ (Λ • A) ε ν = distDeriv μ Λ ε ν • A (ε • ν) + Λ (ε • ν) • distDeriv μ A ε ν
  -- Since distDeriv μ Λ ε ν = 0 (because Λ is a constant), the first term is zero.
  -- So distDeriv μ (Λ • A) ε ν = Λ (ε • ν) • distDeriv μ A ε ν
  -- This means that the two expressions are equal.
  simp [distDeriv_const_mul]
